/*  Blood Management System */

The Blood Management System is a software application designed to manage and streamline the processes involved in blood donation and transfusion. 
It helps organizations track blood donors, manage blood inventories, and facilitate blood requests for patients in need. 
This system aims to enhance the efficiency of blood banks and ensure timely availability of blood for emergencies.

Features
	Donor Management: Register new donors, update donor information, and view donor details.
    Blood Inventory Management: Track available blood types and quantities, manage inventory levels, and record blood donations.
    Request Management: Handle blood requests from hospitals and patients, and allocate blood units based on availability.
    Reporting: Generate reports on donor statistics, blood inventory, and request fulfillment.
    User Management: Manage user roles and permissions to ensure secure access to system functionalities.